847
00:54:21,190 --> 00:54:36,590
Rym: Well, I guess I'm always, I never like when a half-assed version of a feature is put into an inappropriate device, as opposed to, most people probably don't need this feature, and if people who really want or need it get a dedicated, specialized device to do that thing.

848
00:54:36,690 --> 00:54:42,290
Rym: Like, if I were that guy, I would have a specialized ice maker, like, in my bar.

849
00:54:43,471 --> 00:54:50,690
Scott: Well, I mean, if you are in a place where, you know, let's say, you know, the water is not so drinkable from the tap, right?

850
00:54:51,794 --> 00:54:52,035
Scott: Yeah.

851
00:54:52,116 --> 00:54:54,730
Rym: And you want to filter it and keep it cold.

852
00:54:55,070 --> 00:54:57,819
Scott: Even for me, like, my water is drinkable from the tap.

853
00:54:57,880 --> 00:55:00,950
Scott: I'm in New York City, like, the best water, among the best waters, right?

